<task id="038" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Swap `sprk_communication` default form with Form Component Control → EmailComposer Code Page (Surface 2)</title>
    <phase>Wave 2 — EmailComposer Code Page + Entry Surfaces</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>035, 036</dependencies>
    <blocks>039, 042</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, deploy, code-page</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Dataverse customization change; reversible per NFR-07; tested via dev smoke test; gated by UQ1 audit in task 035</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>H</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Parallel-safe with 037 (ribbon) and 040 (embeddable docs) — independent Dataverse customizations and independent outputs</parallel-reason>
    <fr-refs>FR-19 (Surface 2), NFR-07</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Configure a Form Component Control (or equivalent custom-page form binding) that replaces the default `sprk_communication` standard form. Navigating to a `sprk_communication` record opens the EmailComposer Code Page in `mode=view&id={recordGuid}`.

    Per NFR-07 (reversibility), the standard form MUST be retained as a hidden/admin-only fallback. Task 039 documents the fallback access mechanism. Per task 035 (UQ1 audit), confirm the audit's recommendation supports proceeding — if escalated, do not proceed without owner sign-off.

    The swap should be reversible: an admin can switch back to the standard form by changing form order / form visibility without code changes.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke Dataverse customization engineer. Familiar with Form Component Control (or Custom Page form binding), form order / form visibility / security role assignment, and reversibility patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Opening any `sprk_communication` record in the unified interface (model-driven app) loads the EmailComposer Code Page with `mode=view&id={recordGuid}` instead of the standard form. Standard form retained as the second (hidden) form, available to admin/debug roles only. NFR-07 (reversibility) verified by toggle-back smoke test.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-19 Surface 2, navigating to a `sprk_communication` record should open the Code Page (the canonical Communication form per ADR-033). The mechanism in Dataverse: Form Component Control bound to a Custom Page web resource, OR primary form replacement with the Code Page hosted as the new "Information" form.

      The exact mechanism depends on the empirical state of the dev environment + Dataverse capabilities at the time of execution. Two options:
      - **Option A**: Form Component Control (preferred per FR-19 wording) — a control on the form binds to the Custom Page
      - **Option B**: Replace primary form with a new custom form whose only content is an iframe/embed pointing to the Code Page

      Choose the option that delivers FR-19 with least breakage to existing customizations (per task 035's audit). If both are viable, prefer Option A.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>(Dataverse) sprk_communication entity form definitions (UPDATED — add new form or modify primary form)</file>
      <file>(Dataverse) Form order changed: new form primary; standard form hidden/admin-only</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/035-form-customization-audit.md (INPUT — UQ1 audit findings)</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/038-form-swap-deploy.md (NEW)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-19 Surface 2">Form Component Control or equivalent — opens Code Page with `mode=view&id={recordGuid}`</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-07">Reversibility — standard form retained as admin fallback; swap reversible without code change</constraint>
    <constraint source="UQ1 gate (task 035)">If audit recommendation is "escalate", BLOCK on owner sign-off before proceeding</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-026">Code Page is full-page; the form binding hosts it in lieu of the standard form</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Auth bootstrap handled by Code Page; form binding does not interfere</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Dev environment only</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No `.claude/` writes in this Wave 2 task</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
