  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Opening `sprk_communication` record loads EmailComposer Code Page in view mode (verified in dev).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Record ID correctly passed via `data=` URL param; Code Page loads correct record.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Standard form retained as fallback; accessible to admin role (per task 039 doc).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Swap reversibility verified: form order toggle restores standard form access without code change.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">UQ1 audit recommendation honored (proceed / mitigations applied / escalation cleared).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Smoke-test note documents results.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No `.claude/` files modified in this task.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Parallel-group H: 037 (ribbon) and 040 (docs) are safe to run alongside. None of the three modify the same Dataverse customization surface.

    The Form Component Control mechanism may require a unified-interface-specific configuration that differs between dev tenants — adapt to the actual capabilities present in dev.

    If Option A (Form Component Control) is not available in the dev environment, fall back to Option B (primary form with embed). Document the choice.
